events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: J.K. Dobbins broke Ohio State's freshman record by rushing for 181 yards in his college debut, J.T. Barrett threw three touchdown passes and the second-ranked Buckeyes pulled away to beat Indiana 49-21 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 2 Ohio State pulls away to beat Indiana 49-21

events.name: Tulsa Golden Hurricane at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Mason Rudolph threw for 303 yards and three touchdowns and ran for another score to help No. 10 Oklahoma State beat Tulsa 59-24 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rudolph leads No. 10 Oklahoma State past Tulsa, 59-24

events.name: Florida Intl Golden Panthers at UCF Knights

headlines.description: McKenzie Milton threw for four touchdowns and 360 yards, and Central Florida routed Florida International 61-17 in Thursday night's season opener to spoil coach Butch Davis' return to the field for the first time since 2010.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCF routs FIU 61-17, spoiling Butch Davis' return

events.name: Presbyterian College Blue Hose at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: John Wolford threw for three touchdowns and ran for another, and Wake Forest opened its season by routing Presbyterian 51-7 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wolford accounts for 4 TDs, Wake routs Presbyterian 51-7

video.headline: Wake Forest's Dortch gets his second TD

events.name: Buffalo Bulls at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: Tyler Johnson had a 61-yard touchdown reception from Conor Rhoda in the first quarter to give Minnesota a spark in coach P.J. Fleck's first game, and the Gophers grinded out a 17-7 victory over Buffalo in the season opener on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gophers grind out 17-7 win vs. Buffalo in Fleck's debut

events.name: Austin Peay Governors at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Hayden Moore was told by first-year Cincinnati head coach Luke Fickell that he won the quarterback job over Ross Trail last week.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luke Fickell wins debut with Cincinnati

video.headline: Cincinnati's Moore throws third TD pass of game

events.name: Tennessee State Tigers at Georgia State Panthers

headlines.description: Seth Rowland and Treon Harris had touchdown runs and Tennessee State came up with a huge defensive stand, ruining Georgia State's debut at the stadium formerly known as Turner Field with a 17-10 victory Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tennessee St ruins Georgia St's debut at former Turner Field

headlines.description: Diontae Johnson returned the second-half kickoff 99 yards to break open a close game and Toledo opened the season with a 47-13 win over Elon on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Johnson's 99-yard return sparks Toledo to victory over Elon

video.headline: Johnson takes kickoff 99 yards to the house to start second half

events.name: Rhode Island Rams at Central Michigan Chippewas

headlines.description: Devon Spalding scored from 4 yards out in the third overtime to lift Central Michigan to a 30-27 win over Rhode Island in its season opener Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Central Michigan needs 3 OTs to stop Rhode Island, 30-27

video.headline: Spalding wins it in 3OT for CMU

events.name: North Dakota Fighting Hawks at Utah Utes

headlines.description: Utah quarterback Tyler Huntley threw for 227 yards, rushed for 70 and accounted for three touchdowns as the Utes overwhelmed FCS North Dakota 37-16 in the season opener for both teams Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Huntley leads Utah to 37-16 win over North Dakota

video.headline: Huntley throws his first career touchdown pass

events.name: Holy Cross Crusaders at UConn Huskies

headlines.description: Fifth-year senior Bryant Shirreffs came off the bench to lead UConn on three second-half scoring drives and the Huskies came from behind to beat Holy Cross 27-20 on Thursday night in Randy Edsall's return as head coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: UConn rallies to beat Holy Cross 27-20 in Edsall's return

video.headline: Backup QB brings Huskies to lead

events.name: Florida A&M Rattlers at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Freshman Chase Hayden rushed for 120 yards and a touchdown in his collegiate debut as Arkansas opened its season with a 49-7 win over Florida A&M on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hayden shines in debut as Arkansas downs Florida A&M 49-7

video.headline: Hayden stretches out for a 5-yard TD

events.name: Louisiana Monroe Warhawks at Memphis Tigers

headlines.description: Darrell Henderson rushed for 169 yards and two long touchdowns, and Tony Pollard returned a kickoff 99 yards to lead Memphis to a 37-29 win over Louisiana Monroe in the season opener on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Henderson, Memphis run past Louisiana Monroe 37-29

events.name: New Mexico State Aggies at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: Manny Wilkins threw for 300 yards and two touchdowns, Kalen Ballage had two scoring runs and Arizona State overcame a sluggish second quarter to open the season with a 37-31 victory over New Mexico State on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arizona State knocks off New Mexico State 37-31 in opener

video.headline: Spectacular one-handed catch for New Mexico State
